Text:
GoodSync is asking for a Name and Order ID, as you cannot proceed without these, and the activation is online direct or via a browser.

The Keygen wants a request code before it can generate an activation code.

I'm normally good with keygen, but cannot figure this out at all.

What are we supposed to do?
PS The latest version is 9.4.8.8, although neither work with this Keygen as they both activate in the same manner.

Terratec1234, it works with the latest version. Select 'online via browser', enter a random order number and name, and copy the code that it gives you on the next screen and copy it into the keygen. The keygen should spit out a string at you. Just copy that into the goodsync window and it will activate!
Also, it does not seem that 9.4.8.8 is a required update, as I had to do the update manually.

For some bizarre reason, I was trying to guess an Order Code (xxx-xxx-xxx-xxx) which got denied for me.

The Order ID method DOES work.

Thanks for that :)
